
What git command creates a branch?
git checkout -b 'branch_name'

What is the difference between a fast-forward and recursive merge?
fast-forward is easiest way to commit, but when you have  commits on different branches (not chronological) then recursive merge is used 

What git command changes to another branch?
git checkout 'name_of_the_branch'

What git command deletes a branch?
 git branch -d 'name_of_the_branch'

How do merge conflicts happen?
When you hava different commits on the same file in different branches... you have to choose only one option.
